---

### File 2: The Critical `.gitignore` File
When working with AI agents, you often use `.env` files or local configs to store API keys. If your secret keys leak onto public GitHub repositories, bots will steal them instantly. 

Create a file named exactly **`.gitignore`** (include the dot at the beginning!) and paste this standard blocker code:

```text
# Local virtual environment insulation tracking files
venv/
.venv/
ENV/
env/

# Secret tokens and application variables configuration vaults
.env
.env.local
.secret*
secrets.toml

# Python runtime cached files and logging dumps
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.pytest_cache/
.streamlit/config.toml